50|$|The Peter Dollond {{compound}} chest microscope {{is based}} on improvements to the Cuff-style microscope introduced by British scientific instrument designers Edward Nairne and Thomas Blunt around 1780. Another design was for the Peter Dollond compound monocular <b>Eriometer</b> around 1790 used to accurately measure the thickness and size of wool fibres.|$|E

